    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The 6 non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 requirements. Discretization error achieved level 3 against a required level of 2, providing additional confidence margin. The CFD model is accepted as sufficiently credible to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in the CPB application context. This model has been applied in clinical research to support Class II device submissions.",
